.TH "ib_cm_listen" 9 "ib_cm_listen" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ib_cm_listen \- Initiates listening on the specified service ID for connection and service ID resolution requests.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ib_cm_listen
.BI "(struct ib_cm_id *cm_id "  ","
.BI "__be64 service_id "  ","
.BI "__be64 service_mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cm_id" 12
Connection identifier associated with the listen request.
.IP "service_id" 12
Service identifier matched against incoming connection
and service ID resolution requests.  The service ID should be specified
network-byte order.  If set to IB_CM_ASSIGN_SERVICE_ID, the CM will
assign a service ID to the caller.
.IP "service_mask" 12
Mask applied to service ID used to listen across a
range of service IDs.  If set to 0, the service ID is matched
exactly.  This parameter is ignored if service_id is set to
IB_CM_ASSIGN_SERVICE_ID.
